  SpeciesInfo(nepaliName: 'क्रिकेट भ्यागुता', englishName: 'Cricket Frog', scientificName: 'Minervarya syhadrensis', habitat: 'Near water bodies, grasslands', conservationStatus: 'Least Concern', description: 'Small dicroglossid frogs common in CNP\'s Terai lowlands. Their chirping calls resemble crickets, making them difficult to locate by sound alone.', funFact: 'Cricket frogs can jump over 36 times their body length in a single leap — equivalent to a human jumping the length of a basketball court in one bound.'),
