  SpeciesInfo(nepaliName: 'सिरिस / सेतो सिरिस', englishName: 'White Siris', scientificName: 'Albizia procera', habitat: 'Mixed forest and edges', conservationStatus: 'Least Concern', description: 'Fast-growing legume tree that fixes nitrogen in CNP\'s soils, enriching them for other plants. It provides good fodder for livestock in the buffer zone and excellent shade.', funFact: 'White siris leaflets fold shut each night in a process called "nyctinasty" — the whole tree appears to go to sleep at sunset, with all leaves closing like books, reopening at dawn.'),
