  SpeciesInfo(nepaliName: 'दारुहल्दी (wild)', englishName: 'Wild Turmeric', scientificName: 'Curcuma spp.', habitat: 'Understorey forest', conservationStatus: 'Least Concern', description: 'Medicinal herb with rhizomes found in CNP\'s forest understorey. The bright yellow pigment curcumin in its rhizomes has been used in traditional medicine for thousands of years.', funFact: 'Wild turmeric rhizomes contain curcumin, currently under study as a potential treatment for Alzheimer\'s disease, cancer, and diabetes — over 6,000 scientific studies have investigated its properties.'),
